observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

a.	Submit an explanation about the deficiencies and observations cited; 



b.	Require the submission of the lacking supporting documents on the payment of the benefits;



c.	Observe the terms and provisions embodied in the Memorandum of Agreement for proper implementation of the program.

This recommendation is without prejudice to the issuance of Notice of Suspension/Disallowance.

We recommended that the LCE require:
The BAC Secretariat to post the accumulated reports on utilization of Bayanihan grant in at least three (3) conspicuous public places and submit the said reports or the information on the compliance to posting and reporting requirements to other offices where submission is required;
The designated officials/employees to undertake immediately the required inspection and acceptance upon the delivery of goods and services to ensure that the goods delivered comply with the specifications in the contract/PO, and be immediately delivered or issued to end-users/beneficiaries especially in times of emergencies/calamities.

We recommended that the LCE:
Require the Property Officer/GSO and the Municipal Accountant to maintain stock cards and property ledger cards, respectively;
Require the Property Officer/GSO to properly assign unique Property Number to each item of PPE for easy reference;
Initiate the formulation of plans/strategies for the one-time cleansing of the PPE accounts to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability, pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We reiterated our recommendations that management:
a.	Require the Sangguniang Bayan to pass an ordinance creating a Local Economic Enterprise, out of the operation of the GILTT;
b.	Require the accountant to maintain a separate set of books as a special account in the General Fund for the LEE;
c.	Strictly observe the procedures and policy framework in the organization and operation of the LEE prescribed in the manual / LBC 111.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
a)	Direct the HRMO to explain in writing why she recommended the monetization of leave credits despite non-compliance of the Omnibus Rules on Leave of the Civil Service Commission on the at least five days vacation leave credits  is retained after monetization;
b)	 Require HRMO to  submit  the lacking supporting documents;
c)	 Direct the HRMO  to observe strict adherence with the existing Civil Service Commission (CSC) rules and regulations in processing application for monetization of leave credits, and 
d)	Instruct the Accountant to ensure the completeness of supporting documents in the processing of claims.

We recommended that the management: 
a) 	Fast track the implementation of the PPAs consistent with the MOAs for the benefit of the targeted constituents; 
b) 	Return to the Source Agency the balance of unutilized fund for completed projects in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013 to enable the National Government to re-appropriate the funds to other priority programs; 
c) 	Return to the Source Agency the amount erroneously downloaded to the account of the agency immediately upon disapproval of the SA on the letter-request of the agency to allocate the funds for other purpose.

We recommended that;

Management strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular Nos. 94-013 and 2012-002. Fund Transfers should be supported with the appropriate MOA and other supporting documents in order to properly account the transactions and monitor the implementation of the projects;
The LCE require the accountant to make the appropriate adjusting journal entries to reclassify the Subsidy status of the to fund transferred, to Due from LGUs;
The Accountant require the Barangays concerned to submit timely the Liquidations Reports/ Report of Checks Issued and Report of Disbursement in order to properly account the amount transferred and utilized.

We reiterated our recommendations that management:
Require the Sangguniang Bayan to pass an ordinance creating a Local Economic Enterprise, out of the operation of the GILTT;
Require the accountant to maintain a separate set of books as a special account in the General Fund for the LEE;
Strictly observe the procedures and policy framework in the organization and operation of the LEE prescribed in the Manual / LBC 111.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the HRMO to explain in writing why she recommended the monetization of leave credits despite non-compliance of the Omnibus Rules on Leave of the Civil Service Commission on the at least five days vacation leave credits  is retained after monetization;
Require HRMO to  submit  the lacking supporting documents;
Direct the HRMO  to observe strict adherence with the existing Civil Service Commission (CSC) rules and regulations in processing application for monetization of leave credits, and
Instruct the Accountant to ensure the completeness of supporting documents in the processing of claims.

We recommended that the management:
Fast track the implementation of the PPAs consistent with the MOAs for the benefit of the targeted constituents;
Return to the Source Agency the balance of unutilized fund for completed projects in accordance with COA Circular No. 94-013 to enable the National Government to re-appropriate the funds to other priority programs;
Return to the Source Agency the amount erroneously downloaded to the account of the agency immediately upon disapproval of the SA on the letter-request of the agency to allocate the funds for other purpose.

We recommended that;
Management strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular Nos. 94-013 and 2012-002. Fund Transfers should be supported with the appropriate MOA and other supporting Documents in order to properly account the transactions and monitor the implementation of the projects;
The LCE require the accountant to make the appropriate adjusting journal entries to reclassify the Subsidy status of the fund transferred, to Due from LGUs; and
The Accountant require the barangays concerned to submit timely the Liquidations Reports / Report of Checks Issued and Report of Disbursement in order to properly account the amount transferred and utilized.

We recommended that management:
Require the Sangguniang Bayan to pass an ordinance creating a Local Economic Enterprise, out of the operation of the GILTT;
Require the accountant to maintain for the said LEE, a separate set of books as a special account in the General Fund;
Strictly observe the procedures and policy framework in the organization and operation of the LEE prescribed in the manual / LBC 111 ;
